Girl Who Got Away is the fourth studio album by English singer-songwriter Dido. The album was released in Europe on 4 March 2013, and in North America on 26 March 2013,[5] and serves as the follow-up to 2008's Safe Trip Home. The album was preceded by promotional single "Let Us Move On" (featuring Kendrick Lamar) and official singles "No Freedom" and "End of Night". The album peaked to number 5 on the UK Albums Chart, her fourth Top 5 album in the UK.
